RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y Turf CR: 91. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota B red Claiming Price $12,500. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile and 70 yards on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOVE OVER (GB) raced in the three path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far bend and dueled to the wire to get up for the win late. ZUMURUDEE saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path, angled in to began a bid in the final furlong, and gained ground late from there while also bumping with GOPHER GOLD near the wire. POLITICAL RIOT raced in the two path early, led the field on the outside for the run up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and continued to battle gamely in the lane, giving way in the final strides. CIBERTRUCK saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, swung out to the three and four path for the run around the second turn and gained ground on the outside late. GOPHER GOLD saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, raced into traffic in final furlong and bumped with ZUMURUDEE and was forced to take up in the final strides. CHEST CANDY raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn and was outrun in the stretch. THE RIDER OF HORSE ONE, GOPHER GOLD, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE 6, MOVE OVER, AND HORSE FOUR, POLITICAL RIOT, CITING INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
